<Author>Flyingfingers47
<Content>Great location We found the NH Frankfurter Allee to be in a great location, a short 2 block walk to the U Bann Station and less than 10 minutes on the U Bann to Alexanderplatz, the main transportation center. From Alex as the locals called it, you could get to any location in and around the city by transferring to the S Bann or other U Bann lines. The staff was excellent and the room, though small but US standards, was furnished attractively and very clean. The shower pressure was excellent and the tap water very tasty even to a water snob like me. We loved the Italian Restaurant just out the door and to the right.. The markets at the U Bann Station were excellent for snacks for the room. We especially enjoyed the cheese shop and the bakery at the Real Center. Being an American ice was an issue, especially since I injured my knee and needed to ice it several times a day. The restaurant was very accommodating and provided us with as much free ice as we needed. Our son lived nearby on Magdaleninstr and we often ate breakfast outdoors at the bakery just past his cross street on Frankfurter Allee. It was a place frequented by the locals on their way to work with delicious pastries and sandwiches for a very reasonable price. 
