<Author>philipellis
<Content>Fabulous stay here We had a fabulous stay in this Hotel in early November 2007. The hotel was immaculately clean; bedding  towels were crisp  spotless and the common areas very well maintained. For such a small hotel, the toileteries provided in the well appointed bathroom were exceptional.The hotel was about a 30 minute (鈧?0) taxi ride from SFX airport.There are 2 shopping centres (Ring 1  2) a 10 minute stroll away, and there is an underground station adjacent to these.A taxi into the centre of Berlin costs about 鈧?5 and takes 10 mins.The buffet breakfasts were great; a good choice of breads, cold meats, cheeses and cereals etc, and the 2 or 3 hot dishes were refreshed when necessary.I have one small reservation about this lovely hotel; 2 of our party of 4 (myself included) found the beds  pillows to be much too soft, so if you like firm and supportive beds or suffer from a bad back, you need to think twice about staying here.We had one small problem ( a faulty safe in the bedroom) which the receptionist resolved promptly and pleasantly.All in all, our stay here was fabulous. Berlin is amazing; it reeks of history, and it is well worth taking one of the hop on, hop off bus tours if you do not have much time to investigate the city. The hotel was brilliant; spotlessly clean, well maintained and inexpensive, we would stay here again - but would definitely ask for firmer pillows. 
