<Author>cheekyzippy
<Content>OK We have literally come back from a two night stay in Berlin, having seen the Killers at the Treptow arenaPlusesThe hotel has like other reviewers have pointed out, excellent links to the underground/ train service. They serve an abundant breakfast buffet.Rooms are clean with beautifully smelling bath productsNegatives.The staff were not very helpful! We asked different members of staff information regarding tours of the city and they recommended a hop-on hop off tour. We persevered and asked another member of staff who helpfully told us that we had missed the booking time for a coach tour and recommended us to get to Alexanderplatz. Once we got there, the only option was the hop-on-hop off bus! For those who like ear phones that is the tour for you! People who want a true feel for the city, get to Brandenberg Gate, and look for the red tour. Not only are they free, but you get a real feel for the city, and your guide will give you an absolutely brilliant insight into Berlin's illustrious history. For the record our guide was called Annabel!Again with regards to the staff, small things such as not printing the correct number of us for the breakfast buffet/ not activating our key. The gym. It consists of three machines! A stepper/ cycle and rowing machine. The sauna is tiny! Berlin is a terrific city, and whilst I wouldn't say the hotel is bad, I don't feel it deserving of four stars. 
