<Author>Simba-Mark
<Content>Super Hotel Stayed in hotel from 28th December 2006 to 4th January 2007. As we are a family of five had two rooms, a double and a triple. (which was a double with a fold away bed added, so a little on the small side). Requested adjoining rooms and request was granted.Hotel was warm with plentiful hot water.Close to s-bahn and u-bahn so travel around Berlin was straightforward.Breakfast was plentiful and staff there were particularly nice. All staff spoke good English.On the down side the maid was always in a hurry in the mornings and was keen to clean room by 8am. A further problem was the bed linen was unchanged for our entire stay. Towards the end of our stay the reception area was having a major makeover...a bit dusty and noisy.However would probably stay in this hotel again and a visit to Il Mondo at the end of the road for pasta or pizza is a must. 
