<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Berlin is alive and very well indeed! Our 4 day break was not long enough to see everything there was to see in Berlin but we crammed in as much as we could and enjoyed every minute. The efficiency of the transport system is brilliant, the shops, the people, the bars, the restaurants, all are well worth going back for. Best Western Premier City Con hotel is very good. Helpful staff, nice, as much as you want, buffet breakfasts and everything so clean. Be aware though, that there is more than one Rathaus Strasse. I think there are about six! We went to the wrong one and couldn't find the hotel but some helpful local people put us right. We were only a short taxi ride away. The hotel has a good restaurant attached and there is a brilliant Italian place just up the street called Ristorante Il Mondo. Well worth a visit and within staggering distance to the hotel. Go on a hop on, hop off bus tour, go on a river trip, go the the flea market, go to Ka Da Ve, go up the television tower, go the the zoo, go back again! 
